The 3 Portals
Portal	Users	Key Screens
Customer Portal - Policyholders - Submit claim, track status, book workshop, pay dues
Internal Portal - Surveyor, Adjustor, Case Manager, Auditor, Regional Mgr, Top Management -Claims queue, assess, adjudicate, delegate, reports
Workshop Portal - Partner repair centers - View assigned claims, submit work orders, update repair status, track pay
---------
Option A — One React App, 3 Route Groups (Recommended for POC)
Single deployable, portal determined by JWT role after login:


localhost:5173/
    /customer/*    → Customer Portal
    /internal/*    → Internal Portal  
    /workshop/*    → Workshop Portal
    /              → Login → auto-redirect based on role
----------    
Option B — 3 Separate React Apps (Micro-frontends)
Each portal is its own Vite project — eclaims-customer-app, eclaims-internal-app, eclaims-workshop-app.

Only choose this if:

You want to demonstrate micro-frontend architecture explicitly
You have time to manage 3 build pipelines and 3 dev servers
For the POC evaluation, this adds significant build overhead with no evaluation benefit — the folder structure looks the same and the evaluator doesn't gain extra insight.